        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Build the base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat {{extra-virgin-olive-oil}} of oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and cook for 6 minutes until soft. Add the {{garlic}} of garlic, {{ginger-fresh}} of grated ginger, {{chilli-flakes}} of chilli flakes, and {{cumin-ground}} of cumin. Cook for 1 minute until fragrant.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{sweet-potato}} of diced sweet potato and pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15 to 18 minutes until the sweet potato is completely tender.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and finish",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend until very smooth. Stir in {{coconut-milk}} of coconut milk and the juice of {{lime}} lime. Taste and season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Scatter coriander leaves over each bowl if using.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Add extra hot stock or water after blending until the consistency pours easily. The soup should be thick but still flow from a ladle.",
                "cause": "Sweet potato is starchy and produces a very thick purée.",
                "symptom": "Soup is very thick and dense"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add more lime juice and a pinch of extra chilli. The lime is essential ,  it lifts and balances the sweetness. More ginger also helps.",
                "cause": "Sweet potatoes vary greatly in sweetness; some are very sugary.",
                "symptom": "Too sweet"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add coconut milk off the heat or at a gentle simmer. Give the can a good shake before opening. Full-fat coconut milk behaves better than light.",
                "cause": "The coconut milk was added to a boiling soup rather than a simmering one.",
                "symptom": "Coconut milk has split into oil and solids"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Look for sweet potatoes with orange or copper-coloured skin ,  the flesh inside will be orange. White-fleshed varieties (sometimes called boniato) are a different product.",
                "cause": "White-fleshed sweet potatoes were used by mistake.",
                "symptom": "Colour is pale rather than vivid orange"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Sweet potato with coconut and spices appears across Caribbean, South Asian, and West African cooking. In Britain this combination arrived as a supermarket soup in the 2000s. Sweet potatoes moved from specialist shops to year-round supermarket staples, and the homemade version followed. It is now one of the most-made soups in British kitchens.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
